          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-819908?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">一名员工在巴格达的货币兑换处清点钞票。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：murtaja Lateef/法新社/盖蒂图片社</p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001066658"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/david-s-cloud" itemprop="url" rel="author">大卫·S·克劳德</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">更新于 2023 年 7 月 19 日下午 3:25（美国东部时间） </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-sanctions-14-iraqi-banks-in-crackdown-on-iran-dollar-trade-33ef9f35"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>华盛顿——美国官员表示，美国已禁止 14 家伊拉克银行进行美元交易，这是全面<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/iraqis-fly-to-nearby-countries-to-get-dollars-as-u-s-cracks-down-on-money-laundering-ec366494?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">打击美元流入伊朗和其他受制裁中东国家的行动</a>的一部分。</p><p>美国财政部和纽约联邦储备银行周三实施的这项禁令可能会引发巴格达和华盛顿之间新的紧张关系，并可能<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/iraq-economy-reels-as-u-s-moves-against-money-flows-to-iran-11674128633?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">给普通伊拉克人引发更多经济动荡</a>。</p><p>这标志着在拜登政府<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-launches-quiet-diplomatic-push-with-iran-to-cool-tensions-2f45af3?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">似乎有意缓和与德黑兰的紧张关系</a>几个月后，美国加强了对伊朗的制裁。美国财政部最近批准支付25亿欧元（约合28亿美元），用于支付伊拉克政府因伊朗电力和天然气进口而未偿还的债务，这些债务因制裁而被冻结。</p><p>本周早些时候，五角大楼向该地区派遣了一艘军舰和喷气式战斗机，称这是为了回应伊朗对波斯湾商业航运的威胁。</p><p>美国官员表示，在发现伊拉克银行从事洗钱和欺诈交易的信息后，他们正在对这些银行采取行动，其中一些交易可能涉及受制裁的个人，并引发了伊朗可能受益的担忧。</p><p>美国官员表示，美元限制的主要目标是遏制伊拉克的洗钱活动。</p><p>一位美国高级官员表示：“我们有充分的理由怀疑，这些洗钱资金中至少有一部分最终可能会让被指定的个人或可能被指定的个人受益。”他补充道，“当然，伊拉克的主要制裁风险与伊朗有关。”</p><p>即使按照伊拉克的标准，美国针对的大多数银行都是小型机构。两名伊拉克银行业专家表示，其中一些人与有影响力的伊拉克人有联系，因与伊朗有金融联系或大量参与美元交易而闻名。</p><p>美国名单上的银行包括穆斯塔沙尔伊斯兰银行、埃尔比勒银行、世界伊斯兰银行和扎因伊拉克伊斯兰银行。他们都没有回复寻求对美国行动发表评论的消息。伊拉克中央银行发言人也没有回应置评请求。</p><p>周三晚上，在另一家目标银行塔伊夫伊斯兰银行的巴格达分行，几名排队的顾客正在寻求购买美元用于海外旅行，或者正在接收来自国外的美元汇款。一位不愿透露姓名的出纳员表示：“一切都很正常，人们正常收款和汇款。”</p><p>一位美国高级官员表示：“我们有充分的理由怀疑，至少其中一些洗钱资金最终可能会让被指定的个人或可能被指定的个人受益。” “当然，伊拉克的主要制裁风险与伊朗有关。”</p><p>伊朗长期以来一直利用邻国伊拉克作为因美国制裁而无法获得硬通货的来源，利用其与许多伊拉克政界人士的密切联系以及在伊拉克监管松散的货币市场上容易获得美元的优势。</p><p>自 2003 年美国入侵伊拉克以来，美元大量涌入伊拉克，美元实际上已成为伊拉克的第二官方货币。二十年后，伊拉克仍然将其外汇储备存放在纽约联储，将其石油销售收入存入那里的官方账户。</p><p>据现任和前任美国和伊拉克官员称，伊拉克银行和货币兑换所想出了如何通过欺诈性进口交易和其他计划从美元中赚取巨额利润。以固定利率从央行购买的美元可以以通常大幅上涨的市场利率转售。</p><p>美国官员和伊拉克银行家表示，阻止获得美元对许多伊拉克银行来说无异于慢性死刑，这些银行的存款人很少，商业贷款也很少，大部分利润依赖美元交易。二十年来，伊拉克美元贸易已成为其普遍腐败的根源，因为银行家与伊拉克强大的民兵和政客结成联盟，以确保获得美元。</p><p>去年11月，当伊拉克财政部和中央银行切断其他四家银行获取美元的渠道并对电汇实施更严格的控制时，伊拉克第纳尔兑美元汇率暴跌，进口商品价格飙升，导致伊拉克总理穆罕默德·苏达尼陷入了长达三个月的危机。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-819910?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">伊拉克第纳尔兑美元贬值引发伊拉克民众抗议。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：ahmad al-rubaye/法新社/盖蒂图片社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>这些措施导致通过伊拉克商业银行的每日美元转账（有时每天总额超过 2.5 亿美元）下降了 80% 或更多，因为贷款机构难以遵守提供有关资金去向的详细信息的要求。</p><p>官员们表示，自去年以来对美元交易进行更严格的审查有助于美联储识别出进行可疑交易的 14 家银行。</p><p>另一位美国官员表示，近几个月来，几家银行已停止进行电汇，显然无法向美联储提供足够的信息来批准该交易。</p><p>这位高级官员表示，一些人采用了非法转移美元的新计划，包括将交易转移到不同的银行，以期逃避美联储的审查。他补充说，其他人尝试在伊拉克使用大量载有第纳尔的现金卡，然后运往附近国家，在那里可以以美元提取资金。</p><p>他说，为了逃避审查，一些银行还扩大了对西方汇款公司和中东非正式网络（称为“哈瓦拉”）的现金转移的使用。</p><p>官员们淡化了美国最新举措对伊拉克经济的影响，援引内部统计数据显示，14家银行合计仅持有伊拉克银行业总资产的1.29%。他们补充说，伊拉克的大部分合法银行活动都是由国有银行进行的，该国还有另外 46 家商业银行未受到美元禁令的影响。</p><p>此举的影响之一可能是推升伊拉克非官方汇率，自今年早些时候达到1,620伊拉克第纳尔兑1美元以来，该汇率已跌至1,470第纳尔兑1美元。美国官员表示，他们预计任何增加都是暂时的。</p><p>官员们表示，自去年秋天美国财政部和纽约联储开始更严格地审查美元活动以来，通过伊拉克外汇系统进行的欺诈交易数量已经减少，这将减轻禁止更多银行的经济影响。</p><p>这位高级官员表示：“由于存在更多的真实贸易，而不是本质上基于贸易的洗钱活动，因此我们预计活动的下降幅度要小得多。”</p><p>苏丹尼表示，自去年秋天以来，美国和伊拉克当局对美元流动进行了更严格的审查，导致了经济动荡。但伊拉克总理承认伊拉克银行的弱点，并将阻止欺诈交易归功于对美元交易的更严格限制。</p><p> “不幸的是，我们没有银行系统，无论是政府的还是私人的，这是一个真正的问题，”苏丹尼在中东研究所五月份在巴格达举办的政策会议伊拉克论坛上发表讲话时说。 “这是一个洗钱过程、走私货币以及使用虚假文件进行的虚假交易。”</p><p>多年来，美国官员一直向伊拉克施压，要求其加强银行业控制。官员们当时表示，2015年，美联储和财政部短暂切断了美元向伊拉克央行的流动，因为担心美元最终流入伊朗银行并可能流入伊斯兰国武装分子手中。</p><p>但历届美国政府担心，完全切断巴格达获得美元的渠道将使该国陷入经济动荡，危及其他目标，例如防止伊斯兰国重新出现以及将巴格达从德黑兰赶走。但美国官员表示，他们希望巴格达开始采取更多措施打击银行系统的洗钱和欺诈行为。</p><p> “我们希望伊拉克采取更积极主动的行动，因为我们不希望只是不断地打地鼠，”这位高级官员说。</p><p class="articleTagLine"> ——巴格达的加桑·阿德南 (Ghassan Adnan) 对本文做出了贡献。</p><p>写信给 David S. Cloud： <a href="mailto:david.cloud@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">david.cloud@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 19 Jul 2023 19:25:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/us-sanctions-14-iraqi-banks-in-crackdown-on-iran-dollar-trade-33ef9f35</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/us-sanctions-14-iraqi-banks-in-crackdown-on-iran-dollar-trade-33ef9f35<author><![CDATA[David S. Cloud]]></author><category>伊朗</category><category>华尔街日报</category><category>专有的</category><category>银行/信贷</category><category>金融服务</category><category>法规/政府政策</category><category>企业/行业新闻</category><category>经济新闻</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>犯罪/法律诉讼</category><category>金融犯罪</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>伊朗</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>规定</category><category>政府政策</category><category>公司的</category><category>行业新闻</category><category>经济新闻</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>犯罪</category><category>合法举动</category><category>金融犯罪</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>银行业</category><category>信用</category><category>金融服务</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Blasts Hit Military Base in Russian-Occupied Crimea]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>乌克兰袭击连接半岛与俄罗斯的桥梁后发生爆炸，导致疏散<figure><img src="https://www.wsj.com/articles/[object" alt="不明确的" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><figcaption>俄罗斯连续第二晚对敖德萨发动猛烈的无人机和导弹袭击。乌克兰官员表示，袭击袭击了一个粮油码头，并引发了该市郊区的一个仓库起火。照片：Oleksandr Gimanov/法新社/盖蒂图片社<span></span></figcaption></figure><!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001066046"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001066046"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/isabel-coles" itemprop="url" rel="author">伊莎贝尔·科尔斯</a></span>、 <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/jared-malsin" itemprop="url" rel="author">贾里德·马尔辛</a></span>和<span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/anastasiia-malenko" itemprop="url" rel="author">阿纳斯塔西娅·马伦科</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">更新于 2023 年 7 月 19 日下午 2:31（美国东部时间） </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/blasts-hit-military-base-in-russian-occupied-crimea-c9c1ffc1"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          bigtophero
"></div><p>周三，在<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/bridge-between-russia-and-crimea-damaged-in-overnight-strike-a3431b88?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">乌克兰袭击连接克里米亚和俄罗斯的一座桥梁几天后，俄罗斯</a>占领的克里米亚的一个军事基地发生爆炸，基辅军队正在战场上奋力夺取阵地，爆炸远远地蔓延到前线后方。</p><p>几小时前，在<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/russia-says-it-is-pulling-out-of-ukraine-grain-deal-68190d1?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">莫斯科退出确保乌克兰粮食出口通过黑海安全通道的国际协议</a>后，俄罗斯连续第二晚对乌克兰港口城市敖德萨进行了一系列导弹和无人机袭击。</p><p>俄罗斯政府周三再次对前往乌克兰的货船发出威胁，称将考虑所有此类船只可能携带军事物资。俄罗斯国防部还在一份书面声明中表示，黑海部分地区，包括国际水域地区，已被宣布为“航行危险”。</p><p>周三小麦期货上涨 8%。</p><p>俄罗斯国家通讯社塔斯社称，克里米亚的爆炸发生在半岛东部基洛夫斯基地区。俄罗斯任命的克里米亚州长谢尔盖·阿克肖诺夫 (Sergey Aksyonov) 表示，由于军事训练场发生火灾，2000 多名居民正在疏散，但没有透露原因。克里米亚鞑靼人社区负责人雷法特·丘巴罗夫表示，这是一个弹药储存设施。</p><p>基辅没有发表评论。本周早些时候，乌克兰声称对刻赤大桥的一次海军无人机袭击负责，这次袭击展示了其对前线后方进行远距离打击的能力。这次袭击是自去年二月俄罗斯入侵以来该桥第二次瘫痪，此次袭击发生在<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ukraine-adopts-slow-approach-to-counteroffensive-our-problem-everywhere-is-the-sky-a2e51d7a?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">乌克兰反攻</a>之中，反攻进展速度比基辅及其盟国所希望的要慢。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="467" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-819765?width=700&amp;height=467" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">爆炸发生地附近克里米亚的交警。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：Andrei Rubtsov/TASS/ZUMA Press</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>乌克兰空军表示，俄罗斯连夜向乌克兰发射了由 30 枚巡航导弹、32 架伊朗制造的神风特攻队无人机和一枚机载导弹组成的连夜攻击。乌克兰空军称，共有 37 架无人机和导弹被乌克兰防空系统击落，其中几架袭击了敖德萨港。</p><p>敖德萨地区军事当局表示，该港口的一个粮油码头遭到袭击，装载设备受损。那里的紧急服务部门正在努力扑灭大火。</p><p>乌克兰最大的粮食出口商Kernel表示，其位于切尔诺莫斯克港的粮食储存和转运设施遭受严重损坏，可能需要12个月才能修复。据称，港口火灾部分烧毁了该公司约 6 万吨粮食。</p><p>乌克兰农业部长米科拉·索尔斯基和其他乌克兰官员公布的照片显示，港口的粮仓和其他建筑遭到火灾损坏。国际公司的资产也在袭击中受到打击，其中包括加拿大谷物公司 Viterra 拥有的一个谷物码头。 </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"><img width="600" height="1216" src="https://s.wsj.net/public/resources/images/a9ba2a0b-9980-4b33-a5e9-29503591b18a-fallback_app.jpg" alt="不明确的" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><p>乌克兰国防部副部长汉娜·马利亚尔将最近对敖德萨的袭击与俄罗斯退出粮食协议联系起来。</p><p> “俄罗斯人的策略之一是发射无人机和导弹来耗尽我们的防空系统，”马利亚尔在接受采访时说。 “我们全国范围内都存在防空短缺。有些类型的导弹我们无法击落，”她补充道，她指的是该国没有被能够击落弹道火箭的爱国者防空系统覆盖的部分地区。</p><p>乌克兰总统</p>弗拉基米尔·泽连斯基周三表示，他已责成军方加强港口安全，并要求合作伙伴加大对俄罗斯的压力，要求其恢复粮食出口。<p></p><p>美国周三宣布了一项价值 13 亿美元的新基辅安全计划，其中包括帮助乌克兰保护其港口的设备。</p><p>黑海粮食协定是近 17 个月战争中为数不多的外交成功之一。在联合国和土耳其的斡旋下，该协议允许乌克兰于去年八月恢复从三个黑海港口运输食品，而几个月前，俄罗斯的入侵导致这些出口停止。</p><p>联合国表示，由于乌克兰是世界上最大的小麦、玉米和葵花籽油出口国之一，该协议帮助全球粮食价格下降了 23% 以上，并缓解了人们对战争将加剧全球饥饿危机的担忧。</p><p>该协议还禁止袭击参与该协议的乌克兰三个港口和船只。莫斯科退出该协议引发了人们对俄罗斯加剧对乌克兰港口和粮食出口基础设施的袭击的担忧。</p><p>乌克兰官员表示，新一轮袭击表明俄罗斯试图在冲突中使用粮食作为武器。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="840" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-819768?width=1260&amp;height=840" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">乌克兰敖德萨附近，当地居民正在清理受损公寓楼的废墟。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：STRINGER/REUTERS</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>乌克兰高级官员米哈伊洛·波多利亚克指责俄罗斯试图破坏世界粮食安全，并表示莫斯科“蓄意、故意袭击粮食码头和其他港口设施”。主要目标是摧毁乌克兰粮食运输的可能性。”</p><p>美国国务院表示，俄罗斯退出该协议是为了在经济上惩罚乌克兰，迫使其他国家在战争期间与莫斯科站在一起，并增加俄罗斯从其食品出口中获得的利润，该利润创历史新高。</p><p> “很明显，俄罗斯继续使用粮食作为战争武器。这一次，影响不仅是乌克兰人民，还包括全球粮食供应和价格，”美国国务院发言人马修·米勒周二在华盛顿表示。</p><p>欧盟委员会主席乌苏拉·冯德莱恩对俄罗斯终止该协议的举动表示深切关注。 “风险在于，这会给全球许多脆弱国家带来粮食不安全，”她说。</p><p>该协议的未来仍然充满不确定性。帮助达成初步协议的土耳其总统雷杰普·塔伊普·埃尔多安本周早些时候表示，他将努力说服俄罗斯总统<a href="https://www.wsj.com/topics/person/vladimir-putin">弗拉基米尔·普京</a>重新加入该协议。</p><p>这一安排的破裂对埃尔多安来说是一个挑战，他指出该协议是他的关键外交成就之一，此前一年他一直试图弥合俄罗斯与西方之间的分歧，与俄罗斯和乌克兰建立密切关系。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="459" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-819764?width=700&amp;height=459" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">克里米亚基洛夫斯基军事训练场发生爆炸，冒出浓烟和火焰。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：STRINGER/REUTERS</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>最近几周，埃尔多安再次表现出挑战普京的意愿，本月早些时候欢迎乌克兰总统来到伊斯坦布尔，并<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/sweden-races-to-secure-turkish-support-for-nato-bid-2452c14f?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">批准瑞典</a>加入北大西洋公约组织。这些举措是在瓦格纳准军事组织在俄罗斯发动武装叛乱之后采取的，这使得普京显得更加孤立。</p><p>俄罗斯外交部给了联合国一个90天的期限来满足其要求，其中包括将俄罗斯农业银行重新连接到Swift国际支付系统，以及重启一条通过敖德萨港从俄罗斯经乌克兰出口氨的管道。</p><p>西方和乌克兰官员一直对俄罗斯的要求持怀疑态度，他们指出，在莫斯科暂停交易之前，克里姆林宫拒绝了欧盟和联合国提出的将农业银行的一家子公司与环球银行金融电信协会重新连接的提议。乌克兰不愿恢复通过氨管道的出口，因为这将涉及将大量高爆炸物运送到敖德萨港，造成安全隐患。</p><p>乌克兰呼吁在没有俄罗斯的情况下，在土耳其和联合国的合作下继续签署该协议，但在克里姆林宫本周表示无法再保证该协议之后，目前尚不清楚这三个国家将如何确保穿越黑海的船只的安全。区域内船舶的安全。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="882" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-819767?width=1260&amp;height=882" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">消防员在敖德萨遭到袭击的储存设施现场工作。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：乌克兰总统新闻社/路透社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p class="articleTagLine">—Matthew Luxmoore 和 Alistair MacDonald 对本文做出了贡献。</p><p>写信给 Isabel Coles ( <a href="mailto:isabel.coles@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">isabel.coles@wsj.com</a> )、Jared Malsin ( <a href="mailto:jared.malsin@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">jared.malsin@wsj.com</a> ) 和 Anastasiia Malenko ( <a href="mailto:anastasiia.malenko@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">anastasiia.malenko@wsj.com</a> )</p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 19 Jul 2023 18:31:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/blasts-hit-military-base-in-Russian-占领-crimea-c9c1ffc1</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/blasts-hit-military-base-in-Russian-占领-crimea-c9c1ffc1<author><![CDATA[Isabel ColesJared MalsinAnastasiia Malenko]]></author><category> gfx-contrib</category><category>乌克兰</category><category>华尔街日报</category><category>容量/设施</category><category>企业/行业新闻</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>国家/公共安全</category><category>武装部队</category><category>国际关系</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>风险新闻</category><category>军事行动</category><category>武器计划</category><category>乌克兰</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>容量</category><category>设施</category><category>公司的</category><category>行业新闻</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>国家的</category><category>公安</category><category>武装部队</category><category>国际关系</category><category>政治</category><category>风险新闻</category><category>军事行动</category><category>武器计划</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Ex-Venezuelan Spy Chief Extradited to U.S. on Drug Charges After Long Manhunt]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>雨果“鸡”卡瓦哈尔可以向美国检察官提供委内瑞拉高级官员的犯罪证据<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001067440"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-819862?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">雨果·卡瓦哈尔（Hugo Carvajal），摄于 2019 年，周三从西班牙被引渡到美国。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：泳池/路透社</p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001067440"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/kejal-vyas" itemprop="url" rel="author">Kejal Vyas</a></span>和<span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/juan-forero" itemprop="url" rel="author">Juan Forero</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 7 月 19 日下午 2:13 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ex-venezuelan-spy-chief-extradited-to-u-s-on-drug-charges-after-long-manhunt-9f17954d"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>哥伦比亚波哥大——据美国司法部称，委内瑞拉前间谍头目乌戈·卡瓦哈尔因<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/venezuelan-officials-suspected-of-turning-country-into-global-cocaine-hub-1431977784?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">涉嫌与毒品恐怖分子勾结贩运可卡因而</a>长期受到美国通缉，周三从西班牙被引渡到美国。</p><p>知情人士称，卡瓦哈尔是总统乌戈·查韦斯 (Hugo Chávez) 的亲信，直至 2013 年去世。卡瓦哈尔可以向美国检察官提供委内瑞拉独裁政权中参与可卡因走私、腐败和洗钱活动的人物信息。</p><p> 61 岁的卡瓦哈尔因脖子太长而被称为“El Pollo”或“鸡”，他多次否认美国的指控，称这些指控是出于政治动机。卡瓦哈尔的辩护律师扎卡里·马古利斯-奥努马表示，卡瓦哈尔预计将于周四在纽约南区地方法院出庭，并表示不认罪。</p><p> “为他人作证——这才是真正的价值所在，”一位与卡瓦哈尔关系密切并曾与美国缉毒人员合作过的人士表示。 “他了解这个机构中的人，”他说，并解释说卡瓦哈尔会了解委内瑞拉政府高层的毒品贩运和盗贼统治。</p><p>自2019年以来，卡瓦哈尔在<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/venezuelan-official-breaks-with-maduro-11550791292?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">与查韦斯的继任者尼古拉斯·马杜罗总统决裂</a>并逃离委内瑞拉后，一直在马德里<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ex-venezuela-military-spy-chief-arrested-11555100543?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">反对引渡程序</a>。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-819863?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">西班牙警方在马德里的这座大楼里逮捕了雨果·卡瓦哈尔。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：马努·费尔南德斯/美联社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>曾参与美国针对委内瑞拉官员案件的人士表示，卡瓦哈尔长期担任这个南美国家军事反情报部门的负责人，使美国调查人员能够深入了解委内瑞拉政权的内部运作及其与哥伦比亚毒品走私者、马克思主义游击队、军火商和国际洗钱活动的关系。</p><p>曾调查卡瓦哈尔的前美国缉毒局驻委内瑞拉专员韦斯利·塔博尔 (Wesley Tabor) 表示：“当你看看他能提供司法范围之外的情报时，你会发现其中的内容非常丰富。”</p><p> “这些信息可能会导致世界各地各种犯罪组织的瓦解和瓦解，”现任佛罗里达州名人咨询集团负责人的塔博尔说。</p><p>卡瓦哈尔被引渡之际，美国一直向马杜罗施压，要求其恢复与反对派的谈判，以便明年举行自由公正的总统选举。但马杜罗对华盛顿的制裁和对政权高级官员的起诉感到愤怒，反而<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/venezuela-bans-a-top-opposition-figure-from-public-office-11373568?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">取消了主要反对派候选人的</a>竞选资格，并禁止欧洲选举观察员参加。</p><p> 2020年，美国纽约南区检察官<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-indicts-venezuelan-president-nicolas-maduro-on-allegations-of-drug-trafficking-11585236443?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">指控马杜罗</a>、卡瓦哈尔和另一名委内瑞拉高级官员迪奥斯达多·卡贝洛(Diosdado Cabello)，</p>被指控与哥伦比亚贩毒集团合作，向美国“大量”输送可卡因，并利用该药物“作为针对美国的武器”。<p></p><p>马杜罗政府否认了这些指控，称其为“一系列肮脏、虚假的指控”。</p><p>委内瑞拉愤怒谴责<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/deal-maker-for-venezuelas-maduro-regime-extradited-to-u-s-11634432668?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">2021 年引渡</a><a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/key-financier-of-venezuelas-maduro-regime-arrested-11592078537?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">马杜罗的重要金融家</a>亚历克斯·萨博 (Alex Saab)，美国指控他洗钱并帮助委内瑞拉政府逃避美国的经济制裁。</p><p>萨博也否认了这些指控。但委内瑞拉前检察官和熟悉其案件的人士表示，他和卡瓦哈尔一样，掌握着机密信息，可以帮助美国情报和缉毒人员调查马杜罗政权与伊朗和俄罗斯等其他美国对手的不正当金融交易，这些交易帮助加拉加斯摆脱了美国的制裁。</p><p>美国调查人员表示，他们一直在煞费苦心地拼凑有关该政权涉嫌与贩毒有联系的信息。</p><p>上个月，卡瓦哈尔的同案被告之一、委内瑞拉退役将军克利弗·阿尔卡拉 (Cliver Alcalá) 向纽约一家法院表示，他向现已解散的反叛组织哥伦比亚革命武装力量 (FARC) 提供保护和武器，包括榴弹发射器。阿尔卡拉承认了美国与哥伦比亚革命武装力量勾结的指控，并成为马杜罗的批评者，并向美国执法部门自首。</p><p>事实证明，卡瓦哈尔更加难以捉摸，带领美国官员进行了长期的国际搜捕。 2011年，纽约美国检察官指控他密谋于2006年通过墨西哥向美国走私5.6吨可卡因。</p><p> 2014年，卡瓦哈尔因美国逮捕令被拘留在荷兰加勒比海阿鲁巴岛，当时马杜罗政府正准备任命他为委内瑞拉特使。委内瑞拉政府向阿鲁巴施压，要求释放他，他返回委内瑞拉后受到了马杜罗精心策划的英雄般的欢迎。</p><p>卡瓦哈尔在公开谴责马杜罗在政治抗议期间涉嫌侵犯人权后，于 2019 年与政府分裂。</p><p>卡瓦哈尔逃往西班牙后，于 2019 年 4 月再次因美国指控被捕。几个月后， <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/spain-releases-former-venezuelan-spy-chief-wanted-by-u-s-on-drug-charges-11568653834?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">他在引渡程序正在进行中被西班牙法院释放</a>，并躲藏起来。</p><p>写信给 Kejal Vyas <a href="mailto:kejal.vyas@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">（kejal.vyas@wsj.com）</a>和 Juan Forero（ <a href="mailto:juan.forero@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">juan.forero@wsj.com）</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 19 Jul 2023 18:13:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/ex-venezuelan-spy-chief-extradited-to-us-on-drug-charges-after-long-manhunt-9f17954d</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/ex-venezuelan-spy-chief-extradited-to-us-on-drug-charges-after-long-manhunt-9f17954d<author><![CDATA[Kejal VyasJuan Forero]]></author><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>国家/公共安全</category><category>腐败</category><category>犯罪/法律诉讼</category><category>毒品贩运/交易</category><category>洗钱</category><category>金融犯罪</category><category>间谍</category><category>贩运/走私</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>乌戈·卡瓦哈尔</category><category>乌戈·查韦斯</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>国家的</category><category>公安</category><category>腐败</category><category>犯罪</category><category>合法举动</category><category>贩毒</category><category>交易</category><category>洗钱</category><category>金融犯罪</category><category>间谍</category><category>贩卖</category><category>走私</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Kerry’s China Trip Restores Talks on Climate Change But Falls Short on Agreement]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>美国气候特使来访考验北京寻求共同点的意愿<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001067204"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=AEFDD20E-B8EC-4F14-B1AA-8439E0D73B67&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fkerrys-china-trip-restores-talks-on-climate-change-but-falls-short-on-agreement-f89be8e2&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">总统气候特使约翰·克里在此次访问中会见了中国总理李强，旨在试图重振陷入僵局的气候变化合作。照片：Florence Lo/路透社<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001067204"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/sha-hua" itemprop="url" rel="author">沙华</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 7 月 19 日下午 1:43 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/kerrys-china-trip-restores-talks-on-climate-change-but-falls-short-on-agreement-f89be8e2"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>美国气候问题特使约翰·克里(John Kerry)结束了在中国的会谈，推动了两国<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-china-start-talking-again-with-global-economic-order-at-stake-9b49a10b?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">重启紧张关系</a>的尝试性努力，并考验了北京在<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/china-sets-heat-record-as-john-kerry-arrives-to-discuss-climate-6a35c686?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">应对气候变化问题</a>上寻找共同点的意愿。</p><p>克里在北京的三天期间见到了中国高层官员的游行，并与对方进行了长时间的闭门会议。由于<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/restricting-chip-sales-to-china-could-backfire-on-u-s-industry-group-says-dbb7b8df?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">北京</a><a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/taiwans-vice-president-plans-stop-in-the-u-s-at-a-delicate-moment-886e484b?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">在台湾、技术和其他问题上</a>对华盛顿感到愤怒，近一年来双方几乎没有接触，双方都表示愿意未来讨论气候变化问题。</p><p> “我们来这里是为了解开被卡住的东西，”克里周三告诉记者。 “事实上，我们确实成功了。”</p><p>克里表示，虽然双方都同意未来的合作，但他们无法敲定所有细节。他也没有会见中国领导人习近平，而是出席了一场环境保护会议，并发出了北京方面限制参与的信号。</p><p>习近平在会上的讲话中重申了<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/chinas-ambitious-climate-goals-collide-with-reality-imperiling-global-efforts-11635346919?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">中国的目标，</a>即在 2030 年之前实现气候变暖排放峰值，并在 2060 年之前实现碳中和。但他强调，尽管拜登政府要求加快时间表，中国政府仍将按自己的时间表行事。</p><p>据官方媒体报道，习近平表示：“实现这些目标的路径、速度、力度，应该而且必须由我们自己决定，不受外来干涉。” </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-819853?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">中国最高外交政策官员王毅表示，气候问题不能脱离中美双边关系的整体状况</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：FLORENCE LO/路透社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>拜登政府已将气候、全球经济和公共卫生列为与北京合作的成熟领域，以抵消美国和中国<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-looks-to-restrict-chinas-access-to-cloud-computing-to-protect-advanced-technology-f771613?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">在技术</a>和全球主导地位方面的赤裸裸的竞争。</p><p>在获得北京同意进行更多对话的过程中，克里达到了国务卿<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/xi-jinping-to-meet-blinken-monday-as-u-s-china-resume-high-level-engagement-c898f541?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">安东尼·布林肯</a>和财政部长<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/yellen-trip-aids-fragile-effort-by-u-s-china-to-keep-talking-9b78ea55?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">珍妮特·耶伦</a>在两国政府恢复高层接触之际<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/yellen-trip-aids-fragile-effort-by-u-s-china-to-keep-talking-9b78ea55?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">最近访问北京</a>时设定的<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/after-months-of-cold-shoulder-china-welcomes-blinken-to-beijing-84b51627?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">低标准</a>。</p><p>克里表示，他和他的中国对话者已经在讨论今年年底即将在迪拜举行的气候峰会之前举行的接下来的两组会议。他说，进一步讨论的要点包括 2035 年新的排放目标以及减少甲烷和其他非二氧化碳排放的方法。克里表示，中国的煤炭使用仍然是一个有争议的问题。</p><p>加州大学圣地亚哥分校全球政策与战略学院助理教授迈克尔·戴维森表示，对于此次访问，具体结果并不重要，重要的是持续的、建设性的沟通。</p><p> “这是更强有力地参与气候问题的垫脚石，”戴维森说。他说，进一步的承诺可能会在迪拜或在今年晚些时候习近平和拜登总统可能举行的会议上宣布。</p><p>克里表示，作为世界上最大的两个温室气体排放国，美国和中国认识到应对气候变化的紧迫性，因为美国、欧洲和中国的大片地区最近几天<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/extreme-heat-waves-across-the-world-photos-7cc1544d?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">经历了创纪录的热浪</a>。</p><p>在周二的会议上，中国总理</p>中国第二号领导人李强表示，两国应“迅速行动，形成应对气候变化的合力”。<p></p><p>拜登政府的共和党人和其他批评者一直批评最近的高层接触，认为这是空谈，没有促进美国利益。</p><p>当克里上周出席众议院外交事务委员会时，该委员会主席、德克萨斯州共和党众议员迈克尔·麦考尔指出，中国侵犯人权，且不愿大幅削减二氧化碳排放量。</p><p>麦考尔还指责中国尽管是世界第二大经济体和最大的温室气体排放国，但仍保持联合国认定的发展中国家地位，并坚持不遵守与发达国家相同的标准。</p><p>自担任特使一职以来，克里一直试图将气候问题与两国之间更广泛的外交争端分开。他告诉中国官员，他将向华盛顿转达北京的担忧，但希望避开有争议的问题，包括对清洁能源供应链中强迫劳动或台湾海峡紧张局势加剧的担忧。</p><p>他告诉记者，他希望“没有任何事情能够妨碍我们应对气候危机。”</p><p>相比之下，中国官员将克里视为接触拜登并利用政府<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/biden-administration-targets-power-plant-emissions-in-new-climate-initiative-cb635552?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">对气候变化的兴趣</a>来影响美国政策的一种方式。</p><p>中国最高外交政策官员王毅在周二的会议上告诉克里，气候问题不能脱离双边关系的整体状况。</p><p>王还称克里为“老朋友”——指的是他们过去担任两国外交部长的重叠任期。</p><p>华盛顿智库战略与国际研究中心高级研究员伊拉里亚·马佐科表示，克里在访问期间与中国对话者总体上的顺利互动只会证实批评者的观点，即他对中国态度软弱。</p><p>马佐科表示，对太阳能电池板和电池等清洁能源技术以及生产这些技术所需的关键矿物的竞争可能会进一步缩小合作空间。</p><p> “这可能会让气候与关系中的其他问题脱钩变得更加困难，”她说。</p><p>气候变化方面的合作是两国紧张关系中罕见的亮点。克里外长解振华周一对中国记者表示，自 2021 年初各自任命以来，他和克里已相互通话 53 次。</p><p>去年，时任众议院议长<a href="https://www.wsj.com/topics/person/nancy-pelosi">南希·佩洛西</a>不顾北京的强烈反对<a href="https://www.wsj.com/livecoverage/nancy-pelosi-taiwan-visit-china-us-tensions" target="_blank" class="icon none">访问台湾</a>后，这些频繁的互动就停止了。三个月后，会谈在埃及举行的全球气候会议期间再次恢复，但今年早些时候，由于谢中风和一个<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/chinese-balloon-used-american-tech-to-spy-on-americans-2e3f5039?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">疑似中国间谍气球</a>飘过美国，会谈再次出轨。</p><p>写信给沙华： <a href="mailto:sha.hua@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">sha.hua@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 19 Jul 2023 17:43:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/kerrys-china-trip-restores-talks-on-climate-change-but-falls-short-on-agreement-f89be8e2</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/kerrys-china-trip-restores-talks-on-climate-change-but-falls-short-on-agreement-f89be8e2<author><![CDATA[Sha Hua]]></author><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>气候变化</category><category>国际关系</category><category>自然环境</category><category>全球/世界问题</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>约翰·克里</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>气候变化</category><category>国际关系</category><category>自然环境</category><category>全球的</category><category>世界问题</category><category>政治</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Travis King, U.S. Soldier Held in North Korea, Had Been Detained in South Korea]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>美国人“故意”进入朝鲜而不是面临纪律处分，这给华盛顿和平壤带来了新的挑战<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001066508"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=D69C17D9-A239-4491-A945-60AAB8A04205&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Ftravis-king-u-s-soldier-held-in-north-korea-had-been-detained-in-south-korea-4cded529&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">白宫新闻秘书表示，周二，一名美国陆军一等兵特拉维斯·金 (Travis King) 士兵在参观联合安全区时越过军事分界线，随后美国正在​​与朝鲜当局合作。照片：安东尼·华莱士/法新社/盖蒂图片社<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001066508"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/dasl-yoon" itemprop="url" rel="author">Dasl Yoon</a></span>和<span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/timothy-w-martin" itemprop="url" rel="author">Timothy W. Martin</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 7 月 19 日上午 11:19 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/travis-king-u-s-soldier-held-in-north-korea-had-been-detained-in-south-korea-4cded529"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>首尔——据美国官员称<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/north-korea-us-national-custody-b53b4449?mod=hp_featst_pos4&amp;mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">，被朝鲜关押的</a>美国士兵去年在韩国面临袭击指控，并在拘留设施中度过了近七周的时间。 <strong>&nbsp;</strong>随着一名跨越朝鲜边境的美国人所面临的法律问题的新细节浮出水面。</p><p>这名士兵被确认为陆军二等兵特拉维斯·金(Travis King)，他的命运给华盛顿与平壤的关系带来了新的挑战，因为朝鲜半岛<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-nuclear-capable-boomer-sub-visits-south-korea-for-first-time-in-decades-dc4a8187?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">的紧张局势不断升级</a>。</p><p> 23 岁的金于前一天未经授权越过边境，并在<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-officer-on-a-pink-phone-dials-down-north-korea-tensions-11558287392?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">参观位于分隔朝韩两国的非军事区内的联合安全区</a>时，周三仍被朝鲜拘留。 </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"><img width="600" height="1068" src="https://s.wsj.net/public/resources/images/867c108b-9cd5-4f9d-b318-b15cf01feec4-fallback_app.jpg" alt="不明确的" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><p>美国印太司令部司令约翰·阿奎利诺上将周二表示，军方正在调查这一情况，据他所知，美国尚未就该士兵问题与朝鲜进行接触。朝鲜尚未对金发表评论。</p><p>根据金的服役记录，他是一名骑兵侦察兵，自 2021 年 1 月起一直在陆军服役，但没有服役。美国官员称，他在韩国的一处拘留所被关押了 47 天，并<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-end-of-small-town-america-in-the-heart-of-seoul-11567503006?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">在韩国的大型美军基地汉弗莱斯</a>营待了大约一周，然后被军官护送至仁川国际机场。官员们表示，周一，他将登上飞往德克萨斯州的航班，在那里他将面临纪律处分，并可能被开除。</p><p>据对金进行判刑的首尔一家法院的一名代表称，金涉嫌参与两起袭击事件。据该代表称，9月份，他据称在首尔热门购物和夜生活区弘大的一家夜总会外袭击了一名韩国公民。该事件成为韩国当地媒体的头条新闻，涉及美国士兵的事件也经常引起人们的关注。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          wrap
"><figure class="media-object-image img-wrap"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="639" height="959" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-820275?width=639&amp;height=959" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">特拉维斯·金 (Travis King) 的照片展示在他祖父位于威斯康星州基诺沙的家中。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：美联社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>该代表称，十月份，他涉嫌参与另一起袭击事件。该代表称，作为该事件的一部分，据称他在后座上踢了一辆警车，从而损坏了警车。 2月份，他因该事件被罚款4,000美元。</p><p>金的母亲告诉美国广播公司新闻，当她听说儿子越过边境进入朝鲜时，她感到很震惊。居住在威斯康星州拉辛市的克劳丁·盖茨说：“我不认为特拉维斯会做出这样的事。”《华尔街日报》无法联系到盖茨，法院代表也拒绝就盖茨的法律代表发表评论。</p><p>驻韩美军发言人拒绝就金是否被关押在美军基地的拘留设施发表评论，但前驻韩美军官员表示，他很可能被关押在汉弗莱斯营。驻韩美军负责监管驻扎在韩国的 28,500 名美国军事人员。</p><h3>给美国带来“不便”</h3><p>金如何在短短一天内从被护送出韩国到进入朝鲜的关键问题仍然没有答案。目前尚不清楚他是如何离开机场航站楼的，并在周二下午结束了对 JSA 的参观，这是一个备受瞩目的峰会举办地，也是一个主要的旅游景点。驻韩美军发言人周二表示，金随后“故意且未经许可”闯入朝鲜。</p><p>前美国官员和平壤密切观察人士表示，华盛顿可能无法让金获释。与过去大多数朝鲜囚犯事件不同，金是自愿进入该国的，而不是因偷偷越境或污损国家宣传而被捕。</p><p>美国国务院前高级官员埃文斯·里维尔表示，作为一名骑兵侦察员，金可能熟悉许多敏感的军事行动信息，例如有关美国指挥和控制部门的详细信息或其部队的优先事项。他补充说，金甚至可能还听取了华盛顿和首尔如何评估<a href="https://www.wsj.com/topics/person/kim-jong-un">金正恩</a>政权军事能力等问题的简报。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-819950?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">据美联社报道，身穿黑色衬衫、头戴黑色帽子的特拉维斯·金是周二在韩国坡州参观非军事区的一群游客之一，然后越过边境。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：莎拉·简·莱斯利/美联社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>“这个人虽然级别相当低，但仍然拥有一些朝​​鲜人渴望了解的经验，”里维尔说，他在韩国工作了很长时间，包括在美国空军服役。</p><p>里维尔补充说，金可以分享的潜在信息（如果他选择这样做）不太可能是与战争计划或战斗部署细节相关的敏感情报。 “但这是一种刺激、不便和尴尬，”他说。</p><p>维也纳研究组织开放核网络的高级分析师雷切尔·明永·李 (Rachel Minyoung Lee) 表示，朝鲜如何描述金被拘留的情况可能有助于了解平壤下一步可能的计划。</p><p>对于之前的案件，朝鲜官方媒体花了一天到一个多月的时间才提及美国被拘留者。在许多情况下，平壤选择在面向全球受众的官方媒体上宣传这一活动，而拒绝在国内报道新闻。</p><p>美国政府前朝鲜高级分析师李说，对于金来说，朝鲜可以将他描述为一名对美国不再抱有幻想并<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/american-says-he-entered-north-korea-illegally-1418544534?tesla=y&amp;mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">希望叛逃以过上更好生活的</a>美国士兵，或者官方媒体可以强调他跨越军事分界线的“非法”性质，并将他视为罪犯。</p><p> “这在很大程度上取决于朝鲜是否认为这是一个很好的宣传机会，”她说。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="407" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-819753?width=700&amp;height=407" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">分隔两个朝鲜的非军事区附近的军事检查站。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：Jeon Heon-Kyun/Zuma Press</p></figcaption></figure></div><h3>前 美国人被朝鲜关押</h3><p>几十年来，至少有六名美国军人选择叛逃到朝鲜，其中除一名外，其他人都穿过非军事区。在金之前，几十年来没有美国士兵故意越境进入朝鲜。</p><p> 1965 年， <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/for-a-u-s-soldier-impromptu-trip-to-north-korea-lasted-four-decades-1513350001?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">陆军中士查尔斯·詹金斯 (Charles Jenkins)</a>辞去在韩国的职务，越过非军事区逃往朝鲜。他被用来在朝鲜进行宣传，并在电影中扮演资本主义恶棍。在朝鲜度过了近四十年后，他向驻日美军当局投降，并被不光彩地从美军中开除。</p><p>其他美国人被关押在朝鲜，面临着严峻的人道主义状况。 Otto Warmbier, an American university student, <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/otto-warmbier-american-detainee-released-by-north-korea-has-died-1497905282?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">was detained and imprisoned</a> in North Korea in 2016 for allegedly defacing a political poster while on a tour. Warmbier died in 2017 upon returning to the US with brain damage.</p><p> The last American to have been detained by North Korea was Bruce Byron Lowrance in 2018. Lowrance was deported by the Kim regime after roughly a month of confinement—an unusually brisk turnaround. The move came months after Kim met former President <a href="https://www.wsj.com/topics/person/donald-trump">Donald Trump</a> for the first time in Singapore, and ahead of a second nuclear summit with the US in Vietnam where talks abruptly broke down. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="499" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-819953?width=700&amp;height=499" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Army sergeant Charles Jenkins arrived in Japan in 2004 after living for nearly four decades in North Korea following his desertion.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Eric Talmadge/Associated Press</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> North Korea does face some risk holding on to King, given his status as an active US soldier.布鲁塞尔行政学院 KF-VUB 韩国主席拉蒙·帕切科·帕尔多 (Ramon Pacheco Pardo) 表示，在金氏政权的监视下，金的任何人身伤害、疾病或更严重的事情都可能引发美国公众的强烈反对。</p><p> “This is not like a missile test, a nuclear test, or an American tourist, American pastor,” Pacheco Pardo said. “You&#39;re talking about someone who serves in the armed forces, and we know how important this is in the US”</p><p> Historically, North Korea has coerced confessions from American captives, forcing them to admit they were spying for the US or confess to crimes they hadn&#39;t committed.</p><p> In prior decades, former Presidents Jimmy Carter and Bill Clinton went to North Korea to negotiate the release of Americans. In return, the Kim regime enjoyed a boost to national prestige while demonstrating its power and ability to compel such high-level visits.</p><p> Seongmin Lee, director of the Korea Desk at the Human Rights Foundation in Seoul, left North Korea a little over a decade ago when he was in his early 20s, and he recalls North Korea&#39;s portrayal <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/SB124938154079404323?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">of Clinton&#39;s 2009 visit</a> to win the release of two Americans. Lee remembers North Korean state media stressing the two Americans had committed a crime while reinforcing that a former US president had come to Pyongyang to meet Kim Jong Il, North Korea&#39;s then-leader, to offer a personal apology and an in-person greeting.</p><p> “The impression people got is that these high-profile politicians come to Pyongyang to meet the leader because our leader is great,” said Lee.</p><p> Write to Dasl Yoon at <a href="mailto:dasl.yoon@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">dasl.yoon@wsj.com</a> and Timothy W. Martin at <a href="mailto:Timothy.Martin@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">Timothy.Martin@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 19 Jul 2023 15:19:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/travis-king-us-soldier-held-in-north-korea-had-been-detained-in-south-korea-4cded529</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/travis-king-us-soldier-held-in-north-korea-had-been-detained-in-south-korea-4cded529<author><![CDATA[Dasl YoonTimothy W. Martin]]></author><category> WSJ公司</category><category>gfx-contrib</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>国家/公共安全</category><category>武装部队</category><category>国际关系</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>风险新闻</category><category>军事行动</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>特拉维斯·金</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>国家的</category><category>公安</category><category>武装部队</category><category>国际关系</category><category>政治</category><category>风险新闻</category><category>军事行动</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Thai Political Star Is Blocked From Power]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div> Pita Limjaroenrat sought to become prime minister after his upstart party beat the country&#39;s military-backed establishment in elections <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001066222"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-819845?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Supporters of the Move Forward political party gathered in Bangkok on Wednesday.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Sakchai Lalit/Associated Press </p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001066222"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> By <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/feliz-solomon" itemprop="url" rel="author">Feliz Solomon</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1"> July 19, 2023 9:41 am ET </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/thai-political-star-is-blocked-from-power-thwarting-democracy-movement-9b724830"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p> Two months ago when Pita Limjaroenrat&#39;s upstart party handily <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/thailand-pro-democracy-candidates-push-to-break-military-grip-in-election-f44a367f?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">defeated its military-backed opponents</a> in national elections, the results were widely seen as a leap forward for democracy in a country whose powerful army and its royalist backers have long resisted change.</p><p> It has become clear in recent days that, despite his electoral success, the 42-year-old youth icon won&#39;t run Thailand&#39;s new government. Last week, an army-appointed senate <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/thailands-breakout-political-star-meets-resistance-as-he-takes-on-military-and-monarchy-7435d9e5?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">blocked Pita&#39;s first bid</a> to become prime minister. On Wednesday, his quest to lead the country all but ended as a court suspended him from parliament and lawmakers decided against allowing him the chance to stand in a second parliamentary vote for the top job.</p><p> Pita&#39;s challenges show the persistent obstacles that democracy faces in Southeast Asia, where countries such as Myanmar, Cambodia, Vietnam and Laos <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/chinas-grand-vision-for-a-vast-rail-network-transforms-a-neighboring-country-17f067cc?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">are ruled by authoritarian regimes</a> . The struggle has been particularly volatile in Thailand, where the military has staged more than a dozen coups over the past century and, in recent years, sought to crush <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/new-generation-presses-thailands-military-and-monarchy-to-step-away-from-politics-11600266595?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">a youth-led movement</a> that has more openly questioned its authority than ever before.</p><p> On Wednesday, hundreds of Pita&#39;s supporters protested outside parliament and in central Bangkok, a glimpse of broader turmoil that may lie ahead. His party, Move Forward, is popular among well-educated and social-media-savvy youths that oppose the army&#39;s grip on politics. Many joined or led pro-democracy demonstrations in recent years to oppose military-backed rule after a 2014 coup. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-819844?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Move Forward leader Pita Limjaroenrat, wearing a blue tie, spoke with colleagues in Bangkok on Wednesday.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Rungroj Yongrit/Zuma Press</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> The young people who <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/young-harvard-educated-politician-shakes-up-thailands-old-guard-235d1f18?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">powered Move Forward</a> have advocated for bold changes to the nation&#39;s politics and society, representing a seismic generational shift. The party campaigned on sweeping promises to dislodge the military from politics and amend the country&#39;s lèse-majesté law, which makes insulting the monarchy a crime punishable by up to 15 years in prison. The unprecedented proposal energized young people but <strong>&nbsp;</strong> confronted Thailand&#39;s most powerful institution.</p><p> Since the May elections, Pita has been engulfed by challenges his supporters say are part of the establishment&#39;s playbook to oust him from politics. Last week, a day before Pita&#39;s first parliamentary vote for prime minister, election authorities referred to court a case that alleges Pita is ineligible for office because he owned shares in a media company.</p><p> On Wednesday, as the legislature reconvened to discuss a potential second vote on Pita&#39;s candidacy, the court said it was suspending him from parliament while it reviews the case.</p><p> “What happened in parliament and in court today could potentially trigger reactions in the form of street protests and new political upheavals, and Thailand has a history of overreaction by the armed forces,” said Sunai Phasuk, senior Thailand researcher for Human Rights Watch. “Putting these two things together doesn&#39;t bode well for stability and the hopes of restoring democracy that arose after the election.”</p><p> Move Forward captured more seats than any other party in the nationwide vote on May 14. After the stunning result, Pita shored up a coalition of eight parties that backed him for the premiership. The coalition commands a majority in the elected lower house of parliament, but the role of prime minister requires a majority in the bicameral legislature, which also includes a 250-seat senate handpicked by the army. That bloc effectively vetoed Pita&#39;s candidacy last week.</p><p> “It&#39;s clear that in the current system, winning the trust of the people is not enough to run the country,” Pita said on social media on Wednesday. “You need to seek approval from the <strong>&nbsp;</strong> senate first.”</p><p> Pheu Thai, a populist pro-democracy party that came in second place in the election, is expected to put forward its candidate when parliament reconvenes next week. Pheu Thai has said it will likely nominate 60-year-old real estate tycoon Srettha Thavisin as its choice for prime minister.</p><p> The legal actions against Pita pose a broader threat to his political career. In addition to the case about media shares, Pita and Move Forward are also the subject of a separate case in which a lawyer has alleged that they sought to overthrow the government by pledging to amend Thailand&#39;s lèse-majesté law. The case threatens to dissolve the party, which would effectively sideline the biggest challenge to the establishment but would enrage the millions of people who voted for change.</p><p> The events are familiar to Thailand&#39;s democracy supporters. Move Forward&#39;s predecessor was a party called Future Forward that made surprising gains in 2019 elections but was dissolved by a court ruling in 2020. The court held that it violated campaign-finance rules in a case human-rights groups say was politically motivated. Its leader,</p> Thanathorn Juangroongruangkit, had earlier been kicked out of parliament for owning shares in a media company, in a case similar to the one that now threatens Pita.<p></p><p> Pita has previously cast the media shares case as a baseless attempt to block him from power. He has said the shares in question were inherited as part of his late father&#39;s estate, and weren&#39;t sold because they were essentially worthless. The firm stopped operating in 2007 and was delisted from Thailand&#39;s stock exchange in 2014, according to company documents. Pita has said he divested the shares, which were reported to regulators, after the election.</p><p> Pita hasn&#39;t said what actions he plans to take next, but has previously pledged to continue his fight for a government that represents the will of voters.</p><p> “I think Thailand has changed,” Pita said before he left parliament on Wednesday. “It has not been the same since May 14.”</p><p>写信给费利斯·所罗门 (Feliz Solomon)： <a href="mailto:feliz.solomon@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">feliz.solomon@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 19 Jul 2023 13:41:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/thai-political-star-is-blocked-from-power-thwarting-democracy-movement-9b724830</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/thai-political-star-is-blocked-from-power-thwarting-democracy-movement-9b724830<author><![CDATA[Feliz Solomon]]></author><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>选举</category><category>国家/总统选举</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category> Pita Limjaroenrat</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>政治</category><category>国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>选举</category><category>国家的</category><category>总统选举</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[China Tries to Reassure U.S. Amid Speculation Around Missing Foreign Minister]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div> Qin Gang, former ambassador in Washington, hasn&#39;t been seen in public for more than three weeks <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001066232"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-819750?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Chinese Foreign Minister Qin Gang was Beijing&#39;s top envoy to Washington until recently.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Thomas Peter/Pool Reuters/Associated Press </p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001066232"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> By <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/lingling-wei" itemprop="url" rel="author">Lingling Wei</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1"> July 19, 2023 9:21 am ET </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/china-tries-to-reassure-u-s-amid-speculation-around-missing-foreign-minister-82697971"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p> Intrigue is intensifying around the whereabouts of Chinese leader Xi Jinping&#39;s handpicked foreign minister, with Beijing assuring Washington the recent thaw in high-level contacts will continue despite the diplomat&#39;s absence from public view.</p><p> Chinese Foreign Minister Qin Gang, until recently Beijing&#39;s top envoy to Washington, hasn&#39;t been seen in public for more than three weeks, skipping major diplomatic engagements and fueling speculation both inside and outside China about what happened to him. The uncertainty comes at a fragile moment when China and the US have been trying to restart high-level exchanges between the two world powers.</p><p> Qin&#39;s absence was particularly notable at an international gathering of foreign ministers last week in Indonesia, where he was slated to meet with US Secretary of State Antony Blinken. Qin&#39;s place was taken by Wang Yi, a member of the Communist Party&#39;s elite Politburo and China&#39;s top foreign-affairs official.</p><p> Wang told Blinken that the absence of the 57-year-old Qin was for “health reasons,” repeating a public explanation given by China&#39;s Foreign Ministry, people familiar with the matter said. Wang told his US counterpart that Beijing will maintain open channels of communication with Washington.</p><p> Blinken invited Qin to visit the US during the top American diplomat&#39;s <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/after-months-of-cold-shoulder-china-welcomes-blinken-to-beijing-84b51627?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">trip to Beijing last month</a> —an offer Qin had accepted as part of continuing efforts by both sides to restore lines of communication disrupted by a <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/chinese-spy-balloon-over-the-u-s-what-to-know-11675385792?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">suspected Chinese balloon</a> early this year.</p><p> No date had been announced for that meeting, though Chinese officials had expected it to occur in the lead-up to a potential trip by Xi to an annual summit of Asia-Pacific leaders in San Francisco in November.</p><p> Asked about Qin&#39;s absence, State Department spokesman Matthew Miller said Monday that Blinken “expressed his best wishes to see him soon” during his meeting with Wang.</p><p> China&#39;s Foreign Ministry sent a one-line statement in reply to a request for comment. “China&#39;s diplomatic activities are steadily advancing,” it said. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=9F7AF9B6-88BC-4AB6-B4C8-E0CF0C68E116&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fchina-tries-to-reassure-u-s-amid-speculation-around-missing-foreign-minister-82697971&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption"> The prolonged disappearance of China&#39;s foreign minister, Qin Gang, has led to intense speculation over his whereabouts. Qin&#39;s absence highlights the lack of transparency in the governance of the world&#39;s second-largest economy. Photo: Noel Celis/Agence France-Presse/Getty Images<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div><p>The foreign minister was last seen on June 25, when Qin met counterparts from Vietnam and Sri Lanka, as well as Russian Deputy Foreign Minister Rudenko Andrey Yurevich, shortly after a botched armed rebellion in Russia. Qin was set to meet with the European Union&#39;s foreign-policy head Josep Borell</p> in Beijing on July 10, but Beijing canceled the visit five days earlier without explanation.<p></p><p> Qin didn&#39;t meet with Treasury Secretary Janet Yellen during her visit to Beijing in early July. He has also been absent from meetings with US climate envoy John Kerry, who was set to wrap up a four-day visit to China on Wednesday.</p><p> Qin&#39;s vanishing from the public stage has spurred new questions about the governance of the world&#39;s second-largest economy at a time when the Communist Party <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/china-locks-information-on-the-country-inside-a-black-box-9c039928?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">has doubled down</a> on its penchant for secrecy, making it evermore difficult to access information about what is happening inside China.</p><p> Considered a <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/china-promotes-u-s-ambassador-to-foreign-minister-11672409545?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">trusted aide to Xi</a> , Qin climbed the ranks from China&#39;s ambassador to the US to Beijing&#39;s foreign minister in less than two years—an unusually fast promotion in a system that traditionally has valued experience in addition to political connections.</p><p> Xi promoted Qin to be his foreign minister late last year as the top leader embarked on his <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/chinas-xi-claims-third-term-as-communist-party-leader-11666499842?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">norm-busting third term</a> in power. The Chinese leader in particular valued Qin&#39;s ability to “present China&#39;s position well” during his time serving as his top envoy to Washington, one of the people familiar with the matter said.</p><p> Qin&#39;s close association with the top leader has made his absence all the more intriguing. An information void has fed furious speculation on social media, including around the possibility of an extramarital affair.</p><p> The foreign ministry first addressed Qin&#39;s disappearance on July 11, when it disclosed at a regular press briefing that he wouldn&#39;t attend last week&#39;s international gathering of foreign ministers in Jakarta because of “health reasons,” without giving any details. Since then, spokespeople at the foreign ministry have sidestepped questions about Qin, with mentions of the foreign minister recently omitted from the transcripts of daily press briefings. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="488" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-819748?width=700&amp;height=488" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> US Secretary of State Antony Blinken with Chinese Foreign Minister Qin Gang in Beijing on June 18.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: REUTERS</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> In the opaque Chinese system, issues related to health are commonly given as the reason for a senior official&#39;s absence. Often the explanation is genuine, party insiders say, though it can sometimes serve as cover for political problems. When Wang Lijun, the former head of police in the inland megacity of Chongqing, went missing in February 2012, the city government said he was taking “ <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/BL-CJB-15144?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">vacation-style treatment</a> ” for stress and overwork. In reality, he <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/SB10001424052702303459004577362360212353368?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">had fled to the US consulate</a> in the nearby city of Chengdu to seek asylum.</p><p> Ryan Hass, a former adviser on China and Asia at the National Security Council under the Obama administration, said Qin&#39;s disappearance conjured up “the image of a duck swimming in relation to China&#39;s bureaucratic politics—serene above the water and violent kicking below it.”</p><p> Still, Hass, now director of the China Center at the Brookings Institution think tank in Washington, said Qin&#39;s absence “will not dramatically alter the tenor or substance of US-China diplomatic exchanges.” The role of China&#39;s foreign minister is to articulate and implement China&#39;s policies abroad, but he isn&#39;t the sole architect of those policies, he said.</p><p> In recent days, Wang, the top foreign-affairs official, has stepped in for the foreign minister on many occasions. Wang, along with a deputy foreign minister, joined Xi on Monday when the Chinese leader met former Philippines President Rodrigo Duterte in Beijing. A day later, Wang met with Kerry.</p><p> A diplomatic priority for Beijing this year is to pave the way for Xi to attend the Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation summit in San Francisco—and possibly meet one-on-one there with President Biden. That priority, along with China&#39;s weakening economy, gives China&#39;s leadership incentives to re-engage with the US</p><p> <em>—Charles Hutzler and Wenxin Fan contributed to this article.</em></p><p> Write to Lingling Wei at <a href="mailto:Lingling.Wei@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">Lingling.Wei@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 19 Jul 2023 13:21:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/china-tries-to-reassure-us-amid-speculation-around-missing-foreign-minister-82697971</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/china-tries-to-reassure-us-amid-speculation-around-missing-foreign-minister-82697971<author><![CDATA[Lingling Wei]]></author><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>国际关系</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category> Qin Gang</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>国际关系</category><category>政治</category><category>国内政治</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Facing Possible Arrest, Putin Won’t Attend Summit in South Africa]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div> South African government has been under pressure from the US and other Western nations for its close ties to Russia <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001066258"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="552" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-819838?width=860&amp;height=552" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> President Vladimir Putin with South Africa&#39;s President Cyril Ramaphosa. The ICC has issued a warrant for the arrest of the Russian leader.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: ramil sitdikov/Agence France-Presse/Getty Images </p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001066258"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> By <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/gabriele-steinhauser" itemprop="url" rel="author">Gabriele Steinhauser</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1"> July 19, 2023 9:09 am ET </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/facing-possible-arrest-putin-wont-attend-brics-summit-in-south-africa-34e637e9"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p> President <a href="https://www.wsj.com/topics/person/vladimir-putin">Vladimir Putin</a> won&#39;t attend a summit with leaders from Brazil, India, China and South Africa in Johannesburg next month, South Africa said Wednesday, resolving a dilemma for the host country, which would have been <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/south-africas-difficult-choice-should-it-host-putin-f1de2323?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">obliged to arrest the Russian leader</a> under an international warrant.</p><p> A spokesman for South African President Cyril Ramaphosa said Russia would be represented by its foreign minister, Sergei Lavrov, at the August meeting of leaders from the Brics nations “by mutual agreement.”</p><p> The Kremlin didn&#39;t immediately comment on the decision. Putin&#39;s spokesman had previously said that Russia would be represented at the summit at the “proper level” without providing more details.</p><p> Putin&#39;s decision not to attend the summit will come as a relief for the South African government, which has been under pressure from the US and other Western nations, as well as its own opposition parties, over its close ties to Russia.</p><p> As a signatory to the Rome Statute, South Africa would have been obliged to arrest Putin and send him to the International Criminal Court in The Hague, the Netherlands, where prosecutors have accused him of war crimes linked to the <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-n-court-issues-arrest-warrant-for-russias-putin-and-another-kremlin-official-d3b9cb8e?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">forced deportation of children from Russian-occupied territories in Ukraine</a> . </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=9642AA64-6915-4C7E-973F-5C48F3D0A8BE&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Ffacing-possible-arrest-putin-wont-attend-brics-summit-in-south-africa-34e637e9&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption"> Videos and photos posted by authorities in occupied Ukrainian regions show children waving Russian flags, studying Russian history and dancing to patriotic Russian songs. WSJ&#39;s Ian Lovett explains the Kremlin&#39;s efforts to re-educate Ukrainian children. Photo composite: Kalvin Ng<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div><p>In March, the ICC issued a warrant to arrest Putin and a senior Kremlin official. It marked the first time the leader of a nuclear superpower has been called to account before the court, an independent institution established in 2002 to end impunity for war crimes, crimes against humanity and genocide.</p><p> South African officials have said in recent weeks that they would prefer for Putin not to attend the summit in person while they continued to look for ways around having to execute the warrant. In an affidavit to a South African court published on Tuesday, Ramaphosa argued that arresting Putin would expose his country to serious risks.</p><p> “Russia has made it clear that the arrest of its sitting president would be tantamount to a declaration of war,” wrote Ramaphosa in the affidavit. “It would be inconsistent with our Constitution to risk engaging in war with Russia,” he added.</p><p> On Wednesday, Kremlin spokesman Dmitry Peskov denied that Russia had made such a threat.</p><p> “No, it didn&#39;t sound like that,” he told reporters during a briefing, according to Russia&#39;s state news agency TASS. “Nobody made anyone understand anything. In this world, it&#39;s absolutely clear to everyone what an attempt to encroach on the head of the Russian state means. Therefore, there&#39;s no need to explain anything to anyone here,” he said.</p><p> Russian Foreign Ministry spokeswoman Maria Zakharova has said that ICC decisions have no meaning for Russia and has described the arrest warrants as legally void.</p><p> Although the US, like Russia, isn&#39;t a party to the Rome Statute, President Biden has said the warrant for Putin was justified. US officials have in recent months also been critical of South Africa&#39;s close relationship with Russia, which dates back to the Soviet Union&#39;s support for the ruling African National Congress&#39;s antiapartheid battle.</p><p> In May, the US ambassador in Pretoria said the <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-says-south-africa-supplied-weapons-ammunition-to-russia-c2489d54?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">country had supplied weapons to Russia</a> , an accusation that triggered a drop in the local currency and concern that Washington could end preferential access of some South African goods to the US market. South Africa has said it is investigating the US claims.</p><p> Write to Gabriele Steinhauser at <a href="mailto:Gabriele.Steinhauser@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">Gabriele.Steinhauser@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 19 Jul 2023 13:09:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/facing-possible-arrest-putin-wont-attend-brics-summit-in-south-africa-34e637e9</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/facing-possible-arrest-putin-wont-attend-brics-summit-in-south-africa-34e637e9<author><![CDATA[Gabriele Steinhauser]]></author><category>乌克兰</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>国家/公共安全</category><category>犯罪/法律诉讼</category><category>国际关系</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>风险新闻</category><category>军事行动</category><category>战争罪</category><category>乌克兰</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>弗拉基米尔普京</category><category>Cyril Ramaphosa</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>国家的</category><category>公安</category><category>犯罪</category><category>合法举动</category><category>国际关系</category><category>政治</category><category>国内政治</category><category>风险新闻</category><category>军事行动</category><category>战争罪</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[China’s Vision for a Vast Rail Network Transforms a Neighboring Country]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>人员和投资流入老挝，使其“更像中国” <figure><img src="https://images.wsj.net/im-817243/?width=1278&amp;size=1" alt="老挝琅勃拉邦当地人停止出售蘑菇，观看火车穿过湄公河上的一座新桥。" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><figcaption>老挝琅勃拉邦当地人停止出售蘑菇，观看火车穿过湄公河上的一座新桥。 <span></span></figcaption></figure><!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001062426"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001062426"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/feliz-solomon" itemprop="url" rel="author">费利斯·所罗门</a></span>Photographs by Lauren DeCicca for The Wall Street Journal</div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 7 月 19 日上午 8:00 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/chinas-grand-vision-for-a-vast-rail-network-transforms-a-neighboring-country-17f067cc"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          bigtophero
"></div><p>老挝磨丁——几年前，这个与中国接壤的小镇还是几条尘土飞扬的小巷，周围环绕着热带森林。现在，一条中国耗资近 60 亿美元修建的铁路穿过这里，一座城市正在崛起。</p><p>数十座半建成的办公楼和仓库耸入天际。中国开发商云南海城实业集团正在宣传这个占地六平方英里的经济特区，这里是中国和东南亚之间的门户，由于新火车的开通，这里劳动力廉价，出口也很容易。</p><p>手提钻的喧闹声一直持续到夜幕降临，这时，露天餐厅里传来中国流行音乐的声音，过境的商人在那里喝着啤酒和辛辣的花生放松身心。</p><p> “中国有句俗话说，哨声一响，价值万两黄金，”云南海城高级管理人员何明嘉说。 “中国投资跟随火车。”</p><p>在全球范围内，中国实施了十年的“一带一路”倡议（BRI） <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/china-belt-road-debt-11663961638?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">一直在倒退</a>，许多项目陷入停滞或陷入争议——有时是因为被指控给发展中国家带来了<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/hidden-debt-plagues-chinas-belt-and-road-infrastructure-plan-studies-find-11632866461?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">不可持续的债务</a>。但在东南亚的这个地区，它却生机勃勃。 </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><iframe width="300" height="300" src="https://graphics.wsj.com/dynamic-inset-iframer/?url=https://asset.wsj.net/wsjnewsgraphics/ai2html/eb4e2cde-13c0-46ec-8db3-1b38e1005f4b.json" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></div><p>北京正在规划于 2021 年底开通的 262 英里铁路线，以展示其<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/railroaded-the-chinese-high-speed-train-network-no-one-else-really-wants-1526644804?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">区域铁路互联互通</a>的宏伟愿景如何为当地经济带来变革。该计划设想建立一个由中国支持的网络，延伸至东南亚的农业和工业中心地带，将邻国拉得更紧，并在未来几十年内将其经济与自己的经济捆绑在一起。</p><p> “对于中国来说，这是一个重要的大型项目。这条铁路的建成将表明“一带一路”仍然走上正轨。”新加坡国立大学东亚研究所高级研究员于红表示。 “这正是中国想要向世界传达的信息。”</p><p>老中铁路是北京计划的第一站。它连接中国商业中心昆明和靠近泰国边境的老挝首都万象。北京的目标是将其进一步向南延伸，连接泰国和马来西亚首都曼谷和吉隆坡。</p><p>中国还计划升级一条向东穿过柬埔寨的铁路，并修建另一条从昆明向西延伸至缅甸海岸的铁路。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="841" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-818984?width=1260&amp;height=841" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">开发商将老挝新兴的磨丁经济特区描述为中国与东南亚之间的新门户。 </p></figcaption></figure></div><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="840" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-818988?width=1260&amp;height=840" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> A worker in Laos inspects a cargo train headed for China.</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>中国希望老挝的势头将带动其他地方取得进展。泰国和马来西亚的建设正在进行中，但面临当地的怀疑和延误。</p><p>泰国交通官员表示，从曼谷到老挝边境的一段路段将于 2028 年完工。有关升级曼谷和吉隆坡之间现有铁路线的谈判仍在继续。一条中国建造的连接马来西亚海岸的铁路预计将于 2026 年底竣工，此前该铁路已陷入困境多年。</p><p>世界银行表示，如果管理得当，老中铁路从长远来看可以使这个东南亚国家的总收入提高21%。但<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/debt-troubles-in-laos-reveal-economic-turmoil-in-developing-world-11657877403?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">经济学家对其财务原理仍存在分歧</a>。</p><p>当老挝从中国进出口银行借入 15.4 亿美元为其股份提供资金时，该国已经难以偿还贷款。而且它不太可能从列车本身获得太多收入，它只拥有 30% 的股份，其余的由三家中国公司拥有。据世界银行称，该国的债务总额已达到“临界水平”，2021年约为145亿美元，其中中国约占其外债的一半。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=D53246B2-FCE2-4490-BA93-E459B9066FAE&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fchinas-grand-vision-for-a-vast-rail-network-transforms-a-neighboring-country-17f067cc&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">中国拥有世界上最快、最繁忙的一些火车。但尽管拥有一些相同的技术，美国仍在努力开发自己的高铁。 《华尔街日报》探讨了阻碍其发展的障碍。照片插图：迈克·詹森<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div><p>澳大利亚智库洛伊研究所印度太平洋发展中心的高级经济学家玛丽扎·库雷（Mariza Cooray）表示：“要真正实现这一目标，还需要大量其他投资。”她说，道路等补充基础设施和获取旅游收入的更大能力将需要更多借贷，并补充道：“他们确实陷入了债务螺旋。”</p><p>英国智库查塔姆研究所亚太项目主任本·布兰德表示，该国“不断增长且不可持续的债务负担”限制了其投资重要健康和教育服务的能力。</p><p>布兰德表示：“这些都是真实且紧迫的短期压力，而铁路项目的回报只有从长期来看才会明显。” </p><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="841" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-818980?width=1260&amp;height=841" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">乘客乘坐新老中铁路从老挝万荣向北前往中国边境。 </p></figcaption></figure></div><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="841" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-817244?width=1260&amp;height=841" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">在一家中国丝绸生产公司工作的老挝临时工正在等待领取工作报酬。</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>但在老挝，北京几乎没有遇到阻力。这部分是因为老挝和中国一样，都是由一个独裁的共产主义政权统治的，该政权可以在没有太多审查的情况下迅速采取行动，而且还因为老挝的发展需求巨大，而中国是唯一的游戏。这个拥有 740 万人口、劳动力较少、自然资源匮乏的国家，对西方和日本的投资者兴趣不大，因为它们与中国的战略需求不同。</p><p>火车在老挝很受欢迎，这对中国有帮助。乘坐危险的巴士穿越山路需要 12 小时，现在乘坐铁路只需不到 4 小时，价格也差不多。学生和农民工可以轻松探望家人。一对夫妇说，他们正带孩子去首都的一家医院看他们的农村省份没有的儿科专家。</p><p>老中铁路公司表示，目前已有2000多种产品获准通过该货运路线出口。西瓜、榴莲、木薯粉、橡胶和铁等水果都运往中国。机械设备、化肥、电器和太阳能电池板正涌入老挝。</p><p>列车开通时，中国国家主席习近平和老挝国家主席通伦·西苏里表示，该项目将为双方带来繁荣。正如北美第一条横贯大陆的铁路在农村地区创建了新兴城镇一样，习近平承诺开辟一条促进发展的“黄金路线”。车站建在城镇外几英里处，为城市扩张腾出空间，并在旁边设立仓库来处理货物。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="467" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-818982?width=700&amp;height=467" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">云南海城实业集团高级管理人员何明佳表示，中国投资紧随其后。</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>中国公司正在抢购附近的房产来建立农场和工厂。芒赛 (Muang Xai) 是火车主要车站之一的小镇，距离该镇约 30 分钟车程，山上长满了运往边境的庄稼。几十年来，中国企业一直在周边土地上进行收割，租赁大型种植园来种植香蕉、橡胶树、大豆和木薯，现在它们正在进一步扩张。</p><p>在桑园里，妇女们采摘树叶来喂养蚕，蚕纺出纤维，织成精美的中国织物。去年，一家新的薏仁加工厂开业，薏仁是一种用于制作汤类甜点和中药的谷物。</p><p>当地人历来都是自给自足的农民，种植的稻米和蔬菜只够养家糊口。 32 岁的赛伊·苏利冯 (Saiy Soulivong) 表示，他过去常常很难在建筑工地找到轮班来赚取外快。现在，他在一个新的仓库群里做临时工，公司可以在火车站附近租用这些仓库。</p><p> “我们有更多选择，”他说。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="841" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-817254?width=1260&amp;height=841" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">上个月，中国游客在老挝-中国铁路的主要站点之一琅勃拉邦向佛教僧侣施舍。 </p></figcaption></figure></div><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="841" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-818986?width=1260&amp;height=841" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">工人们在老挝磨丁的一家中餐馆享用晚餐，结束一天的工作。</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>老挝对外国势力的影响并不陌生。它的城市以融入法国元素的殖民时期建筑而闻名。越南战争期间，美国向共产党藏身处投掷了超过 200 万吨炸弹，令其乡村伤痕累累。未爆炸的弹药使村民受伤，并减缓了数十年的发展，但老挝社会在很大程度上仍然接受美国的参与。</p><p>自四月份跨境旅客列车开通以来，来自中国的旅客人数激增。最近的一个早晨，在联合国教科文组织世界遗产琅勃拉邦，游客们在仪式上向佛教僧侣投下干净的中国钞票作为施舍。琅勃拉邦因其华丽的寺庙和瀑布等自然景点而闻名。再往北，在磨丁，这种货币与当地老挝基普一样常见，标志上印有老挝语和普通话。</p><p> “它变得越来越像中国，而不是像老挝，但这很好，因为他们建造了东西，”43 岁的食品摊贩 Noy Keomanychan 说，他从附近的一个村庄通勤，向老挝劳工出售烤肉和松鼠汤。</p><p> “事情就是这样，”她说，“老挝人民很穷，而中国人很富有。”</p><p>写信给费利斯·所罗门 (Feliz Solomon)： <a href="mailto:feliz.solomon@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">feliz.solomon@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 19 Jul 2023 12:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/chinas-grand-vision-for-a-vast-rail-network-transforms-a-neighboring-country-17f067cc</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/chinas-grand-vision-for-a-vast-rail-network-transforms-a-neighboring-country-17f067cc<author><![CDATA[Feliz Solomon]]></author><category> gfx-contrib</category><category>重型建筑</category><category>铁路建设</category><category>铁路交通</category><category>建造</category><category>房地产/建筑</category><category>陆路运输</category><category>运输/物流</category><category>经济新闻</category><category>经济区</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>经济新闻</category><category>经济区</category><category>重型建筑</category><category>铁路建设</category><category>铁路交通</category><category>建造</category><category>房地产</category><category>陆路运输</category><category>运输</category><category>后勤</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Putin Has Been Humiliated, Put Under Pressure, U.K. Spy Chief Says]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>军情六处负责人表示俄罗斯现在不太可能在乌克兰恢复势头<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001065877"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=5179E0B0-4C30-4FA3-B4FA-848FF823B8D9&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fputin-has-been-humiliated-put-under-pressure-u-k-spy-chief-says-894d62c2&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">在周三罕见的公开演讲中，英国间谍机构负责人邀请对乌克兰战争“默默感到震惊”的俄罗斯人与英国情报部门分享有关克里姆林宫的秘密。照片：马特·邓纳姆/美联社<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001065877"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/max-colchester" itemprop="url" rel="author">马克斯·科尔切斯特</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">更新于 2023 年 7 月 19 日上午 7:13（东部时间） </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/putin-has-been-humiliated-put-under-pressure-u-k-spy-chief-says-894d62c2"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>布拉格——英国秘密情报局局长表示，俄罗斯总统<a href="https://www.wsj.com/topics/person/vladimir-putin?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">弗拉基米尔·普京</a>面临着压力，因为他的核心圈子出现了裂痕，而且他的军队<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/blasts-hit-military-base-in-russian-occupied-crimea-c9c1ffc1?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">在乌克兰恢复势头</a>的可能性很小。</p><p>军情六处负责人理查德·摩尔在一次罕见的公开讲话中表示，普京在雇佣兵领导人叶夫根尼·普里戈<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/wagner-prigozhin-putin-mutiny-moscow-march-7072d6ea?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">任进军莫斯科</a>后向他提出宽大处理，这对这位俄罗斯领导人来说是“羞辱”。摩尔说，普里戈任似乎仍然逍遥法外，普京周围的精英圈子存在“深刻的裂痕”。他说，瓦格纳在非洲的业务<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/kremlins-wagner-shake-up-rattles-nerves-in-africa-middle-east-8c917a97?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">似乎仍在运作</a>，但该组织在乌克兰不再活跃。</p><p>这位英国情报负责人表示，他仍然对乌克兰能够占据上风抱有希望，因为“俄罗斯军队目前看来恢复势头的希望渺茫”。摩尔表示，过去一个月，乌克兰收复的领土比俄罗斯去年夺取的领土还要多，他敦促西方盟友尽可能长时间地武装乌克兰。他说，乌克兰的<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ukraine-adopts-slow-approach-to-counteroffensive-our-problem-everywhere-is-the-sky-a2e51d7a?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">反攻进展缓慢</a>，试图减少损失。</p><p>摩尔与他的前任一样，名字首字母“C”，自 2020 年以来一直领导军情六处，他公开呼吁俄罗斯人对克里姆林宫进行间谍活动，以避免站在“历史的错误一边”。</p><p> “我邀请他们做过去 18 个月其他人已经做过的事情，并与我们携手共进，”他说。 “我们的大门永远敞开。” </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-819779?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">军情六处负责人理查德·摩尔表示，他仍然希望乌克兰能够在战争中占据上风。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：Stefan Rousseau/Zuma Press</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>这位间谍负责人批评了支持俄罗斯的国家。他<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/irans-drone-industry-is-getting-harder-to-sanction-500839d7?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">特别指出伊朗</a>向俄罗斯出售武器以换取现金。他还谴责非洲独裁政权向俄罗斯雇佣军支付报酬。他询问雇佣兵是否值得信任。 “如果俄罗斯雇佣兵能够背叛普京，他们还会背叛谁？”摩尔说。 “如果他们向莫斯科挺进，他们还会威胁到哪些其他首都？”</p><p>摩尔表示，中国仍然是<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/britain-bulks-up-military-spending-to-counter-russia-and-china-b7c6ca05?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">军情六处的首要任务</a>，该机构向该国投入的资源比其他任何地方都多。该间谍机构尤其担心中国从全球收集大量数据以构建高度先进的机器学习工具和人工智能的能力。他说：“中国受益于巨大的规模。”他补充说，例如，中国迫使各国交出健康数据，以换取中国制造的 Covid-19 疫苗。</p><p>摩尔表示，中国与莫斯科的外交关系仍然牢固，但这种关系正变得越来越不平衡，随着战争的进展，俄罗斯政府更加屈服于北京。</p><p>摩尔说，普京决定与普里戈任达成协议，让他逃往白俄罗斯，原因是“连军情六处的负责人都觉得有点难以解释”。他说，与普里戈津的协议仍然有效。他说，普京对权力的控制仍然存在，而且似乎没有受到任何威胁，但“他必须意识到，俄罗斯体系内有些东西相当腐烂”。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-819782?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">一名乌克兰士兵坐在乌克兰东部巴赫穆特附近最近占领的俄罗斯战壕里。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：Libkos/美联社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>摩尔表示，间谍机构不会被人工智能取代，他认为人类仍然可以以技术无法做到的方式塑造和获取信息。他说，特别是间谍可以“影响政府或恐怖组织内部的决策”。 “总会有一种非凡的纽带让一个人能够向另一个人倾诉心声，”他说。军情六处未来的作用将是试图揭露那些想要不负责任地使用人工智能的人。</p><p> “C”决定发表公开讲话并接受记者提问，这本身就是一个新的进展。直到 1992 年，英国政府才正式承认军情六处的存在，其负责人的公开言论也被限制在绝对最低限度。</p><p>现在，军情六处认识到它想要招募更多元化、更年轻的特工群体，正在努力建立更公开的形象。</p><p>英国和美国在俄罗斯入侵乌克兰之前也曾直言不讳地表达了普京带来的威胁以及可能发生的战争。</p><p> “我认为不需要军情六处的所有资源就能得出结论，普京周围的俄罗斯精英内部存在深刻的分歧，”摩尔说。</p><p>写信给马克斯·科尔切斯特<a href="mailto:Max.Colchester@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">Max.Colchester@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 19 Jul 2023 11:13:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/putin-has-been-humiliated-put-under-stress-uk-spy-chief-says-894d62c2</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/putin-has-been-humiliated-put-under-stress-uk-spy-chief-says-894d62c2<author><![CDATA[Max Colchester]]></author><category>乌克兰</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>国家/公共安全</category><category>间谍</category><category>乌克兰</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>国家的</category><category>公安</category><category>间谍</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Putin Has Been Humiliated, Put Under Pressure, U.K. Spy Chief Says]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>军情六处负责人表示俄罗斯现在不太可能在乌克兰恢复势头<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001065877"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=5179E0B0-4C30-4FA3-B4FA-848FF823B8D9&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fputin-has-been-humiliated-put-under-pressure-u-k-spy-chief-says-894d62c2&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">在周三罕见的公开演讲中，英国间谍机构负责人邀请对乌克兰战争“默默感到震惊”的俄罗斯人与英国情报部门分享有关克里姆林宫的秘密。照片：马特·邓纳姆/美联社<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001065877"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/max-colchester" itemprop="url" rel="author">马克斯·科尔切斯特</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">更新于 2023 年 7 月 19 日上午 7:13（东部时间） </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/putin-has-been-humiliated-put-under-pressure-u-k-spy-chief-says-894d62c2"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>布拉格——英国秘密情报局局长表示，俄罗斯总统<a href="https://www.wsj.com/topics/person/vladimir-putin?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">弗拉基米尔·普京</a>面临着压力，因为他的核心圈子出现了裂痕，而且他的军队<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/blasts-hit-military-base-in-russian-occupied-crimea-c9c1ffc1?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">在乌克兰恢复势头</a>的可能性很小。</p><p>军情六处负责人理查德·摩尔在一次罕见的公开讲话中表示，普京在雇佣兵领导人叶夫根尼·普里戈<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/wagner-prigozhin-putin-mutiny-moscow-march-7072d6ea?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">任进军莫斯科</a>后向他提出宽大处理，这对这位俄罗斯领导人来说是“羞辱”。摩尔说，普里戈任似乎仍然逍遥法外，普京周围的精英圈子存在“深刻的裂痕”。他说，瓦格纳在非洲的业务<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/kremlins-wagner-shake-up-rattles-nerves-in-africa-middle-east-8c917a97?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">似乎仍在运作</a>，但该组织在乌克兰不再活跃。</p><p>这位英国情报负责人表示，他仍然对乌克兰能够占据上风抱有希望，因为“俄罗斯军队目前看来恢复势头的希望渺茫”。摩尔表示，过去一个月，乌克兰收复的领土比俄罗斯去年夺取的领土还要多，他敦促西方盟友尽可能长时间地武装乌克兰。他说，乌克兰的<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ukraine-adopts-slow-approach-to-counteroffensive-our-problem-everywhere-is-the-sky-a2e51d7a?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">反攻进展缓慢</a>，试图减少损失。</p><p>摩尔与他的前任一样，名字首字母“C”，自 2020 年以来一直领导军情六处，他公开呼吁俄罗斯人对克里姆林宫进行间谍活动，以避免站在“历史的错误一边”。</p><p> “我邀请他们做过去 18 个月其他人已经做过的事情，并与我们携手共进，”他说。 “我们的大门永远敞开。” </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-819779?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">军情六处负责人理查德·摩尔表示，他仍然希望乌克兰能够在战争中占据上风。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：Stefan Rousseau/Zuma Press</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>这位间谍负责人批评了支持俄罗斯的国家。他<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/irans-drone-industry-is-getting-harder-to-sanction-500839d7?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">特别指出伊朗</a>向俄罗斯出售武器以换取现金。他还谴责非洲独裁政权向俄罗斯雇佣军支付报酬。他询问雇佣兵是否值得信任。 “如果俄罗斯雇佣兵能够背叛普京，他们还会背叛谁？”摩尔说。 “如果他们向莫斯科挺进，他们还会威胁到哪些其他首都？”</p><p>摩尔表示，中国仍然是<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/britain-bulks-up-military-spending-to-counter-russia-and-china-b7c6ca05?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">军情六处的首要任务</a>，该机构向该国投入的资源比其他任何地方都多。该间谍机构尤其担心中国从全球收集大量数据以构建高度先进的机器学习工具和人工智能的能力。他说：“中国受益于巨大的规模。”他补充说，例如，中国迫使各国交出健康数据，以换取中国制造的 Covid-19 疫苗。</p><p>摩尔表示，中国与莫斯科的外交关系仍然牢固，但这种关系正变得越来越不平衡，随着战争的进展，俄罗斯政府更加屈服于北京。</p><p>摩尔说，普京决定与普里戈任达成协议，让他逃往白俄罗斯，原因是“连军情六处的负责人都觉得有点难以解释”。他说，与普里戈津的协议仍然有效。他说，普京对权力的控制仍然存在，而且似乎没有受到任何威胁，但“他必须意识到，俄罗斯体系内有些东西相当腐烂”。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-819782?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">一名乌克兰士兵坐在乌克兰东部巴赫穆特附近最近占领的俄罗斯战壕里。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：Libkos/美联社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>摩尔表示，间谍机构不会被人工智能取代，他认为人类仍然可以以技术无法做到的方式塑造和获取信息。他说，特别是间谍可以“影响政府或恐怖组织内部的决策”。 “总会有一种非凡的纽带让一个人能够向另一个人倾诉心声，”他说。军情六处未来的作用将是试图揭露那些想要不负责任地使用人工智能的人。</p><p> “C”决定发表公开讲话并接受记者提问，这本身就是一个新的进展。直到 1992 年，英国政府才正式承认军情六处的存在，其负责人的公开言论也被限制在绝对最低限度。</p><p>现在，军情六处认识到它想要招募更多元化、更年轻的特工群体，正在努力建立更公开的形象。</p><p>英国和美国在俄罗斯入侵乌克兰之前也曾直言不讳地表达了普京带来的威胁以及可能发生的战争。</p><p> “我认为不需要军情六处的所有资源就能得出结论，普京周围的俄罗斯精英内部存在深刻的分歧，”摩尔说。</p><p>写信给马克斯·科尔切斯特<a href="mailto:Max.Colchester@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">Max.Colchester@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 19 Jul 2023 11:13:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/putin-has-been-humiliated-put-under-stress-uk-spy-chief-says-894d62c2</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/putin-has-been-humiliated-put-under-stress-uk-spy-chief-says-894d62c2<author><![CDATA[Max Colchester]]></author><category>乌克兰</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>国家/公共安全</category><category>间谍</category><category>乌克兰</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>国家的</category><category>公安</category><category>间谍</category></item></channel></rss>